track.name: Autumn Leaves
comments: Name a more gifted pianist in jazz...  who's in the top ten.....
Bill is definitely NOT on tour. It's a tour de force nevertheless to play this freely and melodically whilst improvising.........that's jazz. Thank Evans.
Yes obviously Bill is happy with Autumn Leaves. Fact that they're falling and floating, colourful and free like this pianist who has a gentle touch and this tune.......
Sure, too joyfull for Autumn Leaves. So let's call it Spring Leaves and enjoy it.
Autumn Leaves are beautiful any time of year ..........
One of my favorite moments in my own music listening history happens around the 2 minutes mark when everything falls together and shoots off.
I feel my pencil thin mustache filling in. Wow what a groove!
No problem listening at the beginning of springtime...
